  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hilton Sorrento Palace is located just a ten-minute walk from the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8}" title="Sorrento">Sorrento</a> and offers a great choice for both couples and families wanting to stay in this popular resort.</p>
<p>The hotel’s extensive grounds boast fantastic views looking out over Sorrento towards <em>Mount Vesuvius</em> and well established lemon and orange groves edge the winding paths where you can enjoy a pleasant walk or relax on one of the terraces. Amongst the gardens you’ll find a children’s playground and tennis courts. The highlight of the hotel though is its series of six connecting pools where you’re sure to find your perfect spot to relax. A poolside bar is on hand for light lunches and drinks during the day. You’ll find a further two restaurants in the hotel and a lounge bar that’s ideal for an aperitivo.</p>
<p>The rooms at Hilton Sorrento Palace offer plenty of space and have been finished in a contemporary style with light colours. Standard rooms overlook the mountain but we’d recommend upgrading to a sea view room for truly spectacular views over the Bay of Naples. You can also opt to stay in an Executive Room. Guests in these room types have exclusive access to an adult’s only roof terrace with an infinity pool.</p>
<p>Families are well catered for at this hotel. Children will appreciate the large grounds where they can run around and play, and the pool has shallow sections that are perfect for little ones. There’s also a kids’ club where children from four to 12 can take part in organised activities like treasure hunts and water volleyball.</p>]]></description>
