  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>J Restaurant</strong> is a contemporary Japanese restaurant that offers creative cuisine and innovative cocktails in a refined atmosphere. Delicious food can be enjoyed on the lovely terrace that overlooks Sorrento and Mount Vesuvius. The restaurant is open 7.30pm – 12am from May to September (closed Sundays).</p>
<p><strong>Sorrento Restaurant</strong> has been finished in a typical Mediterranean style and offers local dishes like freshly-caught fish, artisan cheeses and deserts made using the famous Sorrentine lemons. It’s open between 12pm to 11pm every day.</p>
<p><strong>La Pagoda Bar &amp; Restaurant</strong> is a casual poolside restaurant that serves fresh salads, pasta and wood-fired pizza as well as homemade gealto. It’s open 9am – 6pm.</p>
<p><strong>Sorrento Lounge</strong> is a comfortable space where you can enjoy a wide selection of local and international drinks whilst listening to live piano music. It’s open from 9am – 1am.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pools &amp; Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>The six connecting pools at Hilton Sorrento Palace are a fantastic feature. They overlook Sorrento’s coast and the Bay of Naples and there’s plenty of sun loungers and shaded spots under lemon and orange trees. The pool is open from April to October between 9am and 6pm (weather permitting). Guests can also use the indoor pool that is open year round and inspired by ancient Roman Baths.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<p>Activities at the hotel include floodlit tennis courts that can be converted into a five-a-side football pitch and a 24-hour gym.</p>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Kidz Paradise Club </strong>offers fun activities for children ages four to 12 years including water games, treasure hunts and friendly sports tournaments. It's open from mid June to mid September between 10.30am - 12.30pm and 1.30pm - 5pm and is free of charge.</p>
<p>You'll also find a children's playground in the gardens and the restaurants have children's menu options.</p>]]></familyDescription>
